# .gitignore — minimal-realtime-kit
# A bring-your-own-key (BYOK) open-source Swift/iOS starter kit.
# Distilled from snippets/config/gitignore.template + standard GitHub Swift/Xcode ignores.

# === macOS / Finder junk ===
.DS_Store

# === Xcode user & build artifacts ===
xcuserdata/
*.xcuserstate
*.xcscmblueprint
*.moved-aside
DerivedData/
build/

# === Swift Package Manager ===
.build/
.spm-cache/

# === BRING-YOUR-OWN-KEY: never commit real secrets ===
# Copy the *.example / *.template files, then fill in YOUR OWN keys locally.
Config/Secrets.xcconfig
**/*.local.xcconfig
**/*.local.swift
Secrets.swift
Secrets.local.*
*.secrets

# === Cloned reference projects (inspiration only — never part of the app target) ===
reference/

# === Always keep the redacted template/example files tracked (defensive) ===
!**/*.example
!**/*.template
